11,"xml:id":216,"ref":217},"JP","http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537",{"_":219,"xml:id":220,"ref":221},"James Cummings","JCu","http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6686-3728",{"_":223,"xml:id":224,"ref":225},"Tuuli Ahlholm","TA","https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8417-7089",{"_":227,"xml:id":228,"ref":229},"Simona Stoyanova","SS","https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3914-9569",{"_":231,"xml:id":232,"ref":233},"Alfredo Tosques","AT","https://orcid.org/0009-0009-2753-4014",{"_":235,"when":236,"who":212},"Jonathan Prag added metadata, image, and translations and comment of Alfredo Tosques","2025-12-02",{"n":112,"url":113,"height":114,"width":115,"desc":116,"surfaceType":117},[239],{"atLeast":240,"atMost":241},68,75,[243,244,245,246,247,248],"Maggiore, 1829, Su di alcune iscrizioni latine ritrovate in Tindari","Mommsen, 1883, CIL","Bivona, 1970, ILMusPalermo","Raepsaet-Charlier, 1974, A propos du récent catalogue d'inscriptions latines du musée de Palerme","Manganaro, 1988, La Sicilia da Sesto Pompeo a Diocleziano","Fasolo, 2013, Tyndaris e il suo territorio. Volume 1. Introduzione alla carta archeologica del territorio di Tindari",[250,251,252,253,254,255],"T4NR9UP5","GQN8UZSI","FZWWPUD6","PZHQV5MN","RZSFKACR","X2SEXMRX",[257,258,259,28,38,42,260,261,262,263,264,265,266,138],"isic000063","honours for the emperor trajan",{"_":5},"tyndaris","tindari","sicilia","sicily","palermo","museo archeologico regionale antonino salinas","latin",[],{"title":269,"body":270,"divs":271,"editions":298,"images":308,"handnote":314},"ISic000063. Honours for the Emperor Trajan","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Tuuli Ahlholm; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/FZWWPUD6\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/FZWWPUD6\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Imp(erator) ❦ Caesar ❦ divi ❦ Nervae ❦ \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>❦ f(ilius) ❦ Nerva ❦ Traianus ❦ Aug(ustus) ❦ \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>Germanicus ❦ Dacicus ❦ \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>pontifex maximus ❦ \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>tr(ibunicia) ❦ pot(estate) ❦ \u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">VII\u003C/span> ❦ imp(erator) ❦ \u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">IIII\u003C/span> ❦ \u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>co(n)s(ul) ❦ V ❦ p(ater) ❦ p(atriae) ❦ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Tuuli Ahlholm; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/FZWWPUD6\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/FZWWPUD6\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>IMP❦CAESAR❦DIVI❦NERVAE❦\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>❦F❦NERVA❦TRAIANUS❦AUG❦\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>GERMANICUS❦DACICUS❦\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>PONTIFEXMAXIMUS❦\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>TR❦POT❦\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">VII\u003C/span>❦IMP❦\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">IIII\u003C/span>❦\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>COS❦V❦P❦P❦\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000063_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2022-05-23\" src=\"ISic000063_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000063.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2022-05-23\" src=\"ISic000063-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text of IMusPalermo\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0009-0009-2753-4014\">Alfredo Tosques\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Emperor Caesar, son of the deified Nerva, Nerva Trajan Augustus Germanicus Dacicus, Pontifex Maximus, holding tribunician power for the seventh time, acclaimed imperator for the fourth time, consul for the fifth time, father of the fatherland.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0009-0009-2753-4014\">Alfredo Tosques\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>L’imperatore Cesare, figlio del divo Nerva, Nerva Traiano Augusto Germanico Dacico, pontefice massimo, investito della potestà tribunizia per la settima volta, imperatore per la quarta volta, console per la quinta volta, padre della patria.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Roman imperial dedications normally follow a very rigid structure, with the emperor and his full titulature in the dative case at the beginning, followed by the dedicants in the nominative at the end of the text. In this inscription, however, the Emperor appears unusually in the nominative, with no dedicants mentioned. This may indicate that the inscription commemorated an act of imperial euergetism (public benefaction) carried out by the Emperor himself. If this were the case, as the agent rather than the dedicatee, the use of the nominative would be explained.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Maggiore 1829 298 no.4 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002795\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002795\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Mommsen 1883 \u003Ca href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buchseite/650805\" target=\"_blank\">7472\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Bivona 1970 64 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002142\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002142\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Raepsaet-Charlier 1974 126 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001648\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001648\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 1988 73 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Fasolo 2013 71 no.2 fig.32 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002011\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002011\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\"> Line 1-6  68-75  Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[272,275,278,281,284,286,289,292,295],{"id":273,"html":274},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Tuuli Ahlholm; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/FZWWPUD6\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/FZWWPUD6\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Imp(erator) ❦ Caesar ❦ divi ❦ Nervae ❦ \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>❦ f(ilius) ❦ Nerva ❦ Traianus ❦ Aug(ustus) ❦ \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>Germanicus ❦ Dacicus ❦ \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>pontifex maximus ❦ \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>tr(ibunicia) ❦ pot(estate) ❦ \u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">VII\u003C/span> ❦ imp(erator) ❦ \u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">IIII\u003C/span> ❦ \u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>co(n)s(ul) ❦ V ❦ p(ater) ❦ p(atriae) ❦ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Tuuli Ahlholm; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/FZWWPUD6\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/FZWWPUD6\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>IMP❦CAESAR❦DIVI❦NERVAE❦\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>❦F❦NERVA❦TRAIANUS❦AUG❦\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>GERMANICUS❦DACICUS❦\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>PONTIFEXMAXIMUS❦\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>TR❦POT❦\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">VII\u003C/span>❦IMP❦\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">IIII\u003C/span>❦\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>COS❦V❦P❦P❦\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":276,"html":277},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000063_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2022-05-23\" src=\"ISic000063_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000063.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2022-05-23\" src=\"ISic000063-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":279,"html":280},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text of IMusPalermo\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":282,"html":283},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0009-0009-2753-4014\">Alfredo Tosques\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Emperor Caesar, son of the deified Nerva, Nerva Trajan Augustus Germanicus Dacicus, Pontifex Maximus, holding tribunician power for the seventh time, acclaimed imperator for the fourth time, consul for the fifth time, father of the fatherland.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":282,"html":285},"\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0009-0009-2753-4014\">Alfredo Tosques\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>L’imperatore Cesare, figlio del divo Nerva, Nerva Traiano Augusto Germanico Dacico, pontefice massimo, investito della potestà tribunizia per la settima volta, imperatore per la quarta volta, console per la quinta volta, padre della patria.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":287,"html":288},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Roman imperial dedications normally follow a very rigid structure, with the emperor and his full titulature in the dative case at the beginning, followed by the dedicants in the nominative at the end of the text. In this inscription, however, the Emperor appears unusually in the nominative, with no dedicants mentioned. This may indicate that the inscription commemorated an act of imperial euergetism (public benefaction) carried out by the Emperor himself. If this were the case, as the agent rather than the dedicatee, the use of the nominative would be explained.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":290,"html":291},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Maggiore 1829 298 no.4 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002795\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002795\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Mommsen 1883 \u003Ca href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buchseite/650805\" target=\"_blank\">7472\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Bivona 1970 64 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002142\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002142\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Raepsaet-Charlier 1974 126 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001648\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001648\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 1988 73 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Fasolo 2013 71 no.2 fig.32 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002011\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002011\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":293,"html":294},"handnote"," Line 1-6  68-75  Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":296,"html":297},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[299,301,304,305],{"html":300},"Text encoding: Tuuli Ahlholm; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/FZWWPUD6\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/FZWWPUD6\u003C/a>",{"id":302,"lang":138,"html":303},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Imp(erator) ❦ Caesar ❦ divi ❦ Nervae ❦ \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>❦ f(ilius) ❦ Nerva ❦ Traianus ❦ Aug(ustus) ❦ \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>Germanicus ❦ Dacicus ❦ \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>pontifex maximus ❦ \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>tr(ibunicia) ❦ pot(estate) ❦ \u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">VII\u003C/span> ❦ imp(erator) ❦ \u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">IIII\u003C/span> ❦ \u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>co(n)s(ul) ❦ V ❦ p(ater) ❦ p(atriae) ❦ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"html":300},{"id":306,"lang":138,"html":307},"edition-diplomatic","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>IMP❦CAESAR❦DIVI❦NERVAE❦\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>❦F❦NERVA❦TRAIANUS❦AUG❦\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>GERMANICUS❦DACICUS❦\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>PONTIFEXMAXIMUS❦\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>TR❦POT❦\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">VII\u003C/span>❦IMP❦\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">IIII\u003C/span>❦\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>COS❦V❦P❦P❦\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",[309,311],{"image":113,"thumb":310,"title":116},"ISic000063_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":312,"thumb":313,"title":116},"ISic000063.jpg","ISic000063-thumb.jpg",[],"\u003C?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"https://epidoc.stoa.org/schema/latest/tei-epidoc.rng\" type=\"application/xml\" schematypens=\"http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0\"?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"../schematron/ircyr-checking.sch\" schematypens=\"http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron\"?>\n\u003CTEI xmlns=\"http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\" xml:lang=\"en\">\n    \u003CteiHeader>\n        \u003CfileDesc>\n            \u003CtitleStmt>\n                \u003Ctitle>Honours for the Emperor Trajan\u003C/title>\n                \u003Ceditor ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/editor>\n                \u003Cprincipal ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/principal>\n                \u003Cfunder>John Fell OUP Research Fund\u003C/funder>\n\t   \u003Cfunder>\u003Cref target=\"https://cordis.europa.eu/project/id/885040\">ERC Advanced Grant no.885040\u003C/ref>\u003C/funder>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JP\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>original data collection and editing\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JCu\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6686-3728\">James Cummings\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>conversion to EpiD